do you have a daily dose of happiness i do i find it everywhere in a child's smile in eating ice cream in listening music listening happy stories for people i love and care so describe your daily dose of happiness i used to be a severly depressed person but slowly i've come around you see i find happiness in simply being being alive being loved loving others being the best of my potential etc and although i partly agree with the first answerer about their views on happiness being limitless endless etc it seems an idealistic view for many and borders on achieving perfection very few people know happiness on such an infinite continuum i do think happiness can come in bursts comes from within to me eating ice cream on a hot day is like a wonderful release a memory that is a monument to the last time i ate it and who i was with when i see a child smile it reminds me of the child within me or the child i used to be sometimes happiness is about going back into your memories and chasing out the good ones or finding the good in even the bad ones and the things surrounding us only act as memory triggers i wouldn't disregard those moments because they do offer true happiness because it is our way of making peace with the past what better happiness could there be as for eating too much ice cream anything can be turned into a compulsive and destructive habit the ultimate result being obesity i don't see the harm in enjoying it once in a while i mean it's not an evil after all i eat ice cream and i'm not obese good question it was a happiness reminder thanks Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Theodicy A Course In Miracles Current teachings of Prem Rawat Theory of conduct Meaning of life Happiness English grammar Pitaten The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Evil Past teachings of Prem Rawat Bob and George Social rule Goodness and value theory Merit Shaggy dog story Care Bears The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie The Cyberiad Objectivist